cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about text classification using deep learning models. The most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and text classification. The second likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper proposes a novel framework for text classification using deep learning models. The third likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a new approach for modeling sentences and documents using deep learning models. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as the paper uses convolutional neural networks for text classification. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper proposes a new approach for text classification using neural networks.
